ry technologies which focuses on innovative and proven drug delivery technologies optimizing the company’s multiple technologies crossplatform rd solutions and global commercial manufacturing network this is the current structure of catalent’s business which includes softgel technologies advanced delivery technologies and development  clinical services business units catalent announced its initial public offering on july   after raising more than  million catalent became a publicly traded company on the new york stock exchange nyse the company priced its  million shares of common stock at  apiece with a market capitalization of  billion the shares began trading on the nyse on july   under the ticker symbol ctlt and the offering closed on august   the proceeds of the offering went to the redemption of more than  million of catalent’s outstanding debt “this will allow the company to significantly reduce its interest expense enable future potential internal and external growth strategies and to continue our growthbiased investments into new technologies capabilities global development and manufacturing facilities and capacity” a company statement reported in september  the company acquired the contract drug development and clinical manufacturing company which specializes in early stage development and spray drying pharmatek laboratories in november  the company agreed to acquire canadian based accucaps industries both the strathroy on and windsor on locations will become the th and th softgel technology facilities under the catalent name corporate governanceedit senior managementedit position name since president  chief executive officer and director john r chiminski march  executive vice president and chief financial officer matthew walsh december  president development and clinical services wetteny joseph august  president softgel technologies aris gennadios september  president advanced delivery technologies barry littlejohns july  senior vice president chief inform