ently holds approximately  patents and patent applications and continues to expand its offerings through investments in emerging technologies in its fiscal year  ending june  catalent’s customers included  of the top  branded drug marketers  of the top  generics marketers  of the top  biologics marketers and  of the top  consumer health marketers globallycitation needed on july   catalent became a public company and is listed on the new york stock exchange nyse ctlt contents  history  before   formation of catalent in   after  and initial public offering  corporate governance  senior management  drug delivery technologies  centers of excellence  references historyedit before edit in  cardinal health acquired pci headquarters philadelphia pennsylvania pci packaging coordinators inc is a pharmaceutical contract packing service for commercial and clinical packaging in  cardinal health acquired rp scherer corporation headquarters troy michigan robert pauli scherer founded the rp scherer corporation to commercialize his innovation of softgel encapsulation using the rotary die production process in  cardinal health acquired automatic liquid packaging inc headquarters woodstock ill whose blowfillseal technology allowed cardinal to enter the sterile product market cardinal health also acquired international processing corporation headquarters winchester kentucky for its advanced controlled drug release and coating manufacturing expertise in  cardinal health acquired magellan laboratories inc a company that specialized in product development expertise in  cardinal health acquired gala biotech headquarters middleton wisconsin gala biotech had established technologies surrounding gene insertion and the production of pharmaceutical proteins which became gpex® technology in the same year cardinal health also acquired intercare group plc broadening its global capabilities in europe in  cardinal health further expanded its reach in biotechnology and pharmaceutical markets through multiple other acquisitions formation of catalent in edit in  the pharmaceutical technologies and services segment of cardinal health was purchased by blackstone group and rebranded as catalent pharma solutions after  and initial public offeringedit in  the company acquired the molecular optimization platform optiform® from glaxosmithkline in  catalent acquired aptuit a clinical supply solutions company as part of the deal catalent gained three sites in the united states two sites in the united kingdom and one in singapore catalent also acquired all remaining shares for the rp scherer site in eberbach germany in  catalent pharmaceutical solutions continued the global expansion of its softgel capabilities through a joint venture with zhejiang jaing yuan tang biotechnology co a chinabased company and relthy laboratories in brazil also in  catalent created a new business unit advanced delivery technologies which focuses on innovative and proven drug delivery technologies optimizing the company’s multiple technologies crossplatform rd solutions and global commercial manufacturing network this is the current structure of catalent’s business which includes softgel technologies advanced delivery technologies and development  clinical services business units catalent announced its initial public offering on july   after raising more than  million catalent became a publicly traded company on the new york stock exchange nyse the company priced its  million shares of common stock at  apiece with a market capitalization of  billion the shares began trading on the nyse on july   under the ticker symbol ctlt and the offering closed on august   the proceeds of the offering went to the redemption of more than  million of catalent’s outstanding debt “this will allow the company to significantly reduce its interest expense enable future potential internal and external growth strategies and to continue our growthbiased investments into new technologies capabilities global development and manufacturing facilities and capacity” a company statement reported in september  the company acquired the contract drug development and clinical manufacturing company which specializes in early stage development and spray drying pharmatek laboratories in november  the company agreed to acquire canadian based accucaps industries both the strathroy on and windsor on locations will become the th and th softgel technology facilities under the catalent name corporate governanceedit senior managementedit position name since president  chief executive officer and director john r chiminski march  executive vice president and chief financial officer matthew walsh december  president development and clinical services wetteny joseph august  president softgel technologies aris gennadios september  president advanced delivery technologies barry littlejohns july  senior vice president chief information officer michael del priore december  senior vice president global sales  marketing william downie june  senior vice president quality product development and regulatory affairs sharon johnson august  senior vice president global operations stephen leonard june  senior vice president human resources lance miyamoto march  senior vice president general counsel steven fasman october  drug delivery technologiesedit catalents brand currently owns and operates the following drug delivery technologies predevelopment technologies optiform technology catalent micron technologies oral drug delivery technologies rp scherer softgel technology optigel technology optigel lock technology optigel micro technology optigel mini technology zydis technology osdrc optidose drug delivery technology optimelt technology optipact technology sterile technologies advasept technology biologics smartag technology gpex technology centers of excellenceedit catalent has designated the following locations as a center of excellence with the following specializations swindon united kingdom – zydis technology somerset new jersey – osdrc optidose drug delivery technology philadelphia pennsylvania – clinical supply services st petersburg florida – rp scherer softgel technology woodstock illinois – blowfillseal bfs technology winchester kentucky – advanced oral delivery technologies madison wisconsin – gpex technology research triangle park north carolina – inhalation referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n the united states securities and exchange commission  form k washington dc catalent pharma solutions catalent pharma solutions retrieved    a b c catalent pharma solutions  catalent reports fourth quarter and fiscal year  results catalent pharma solutions retrieved    our locations catalentcom catalent inc retrieved  nov    a b c d e f cardinal healths timeline  cardinalhealthcom cardinalhealthcom retrieved  april    pci leads the market in healthcare packaging solutions pci services retrieved  april    a b catalent completes acquisition of r p scherer eberbach manufacturing chemist  march  retrieved  april    a b kuehn steven  october  container innovations prairie home pharmaceutical manufacturing retrieved  april    rp scherer to gain new drugdelivery business with acquisition of international processing corporation cmo cro pr newswire  december  retrieved  april    cardinal health to enhance drug development services with acquisition of gala biotech cardinal health inc pr newswire  oct  retrieved  april    cardinal health completes sale of pharmaceutical technologies and services segment to the blackstone group dublin ohio blackstone group  april    ohnesorge lauren k  january  catalent cements local footprint triangle business journal retrieved  april    catalent completes aptuit deal biopharmareportercom  february  retrieved  april    stanton dan  october  catalents brazilian acquisition supports global softgel strategy inpharmatechnologistcom retrieved  april    catalent creates new advanced delivery technologies business unit catalent inc pr web  july  retrieved